@startuml
title Viaverse Business Account / Merchant State — State Diagram

[*] --> DRAFT
DRAFT --> PROFILE_INCOMPLETE : missing fields
PROFILE_INCOMPLETE --> PENDING_VERIFICATION : profile complete
PENDING_VERIFICATION --> VERIFIED : approved
PENDING_VERIFICATION --> VERIFICATION_REJECTED : rejected
VERIFICATION_REJECTED --> PROFILE_INCOMPLETE : fix
VERIFIED --> PUBLISH_READY : catalog/billing/branch ready
PUBLISH_READY --> PUBLISHED : publish
PUBLISHED --> SUSPENDED : policy/admin
SUSPENDED --> PUBLISHED : appeal/restored
PUBLISHED --> ARCHIVED : owner closes
SUSPENDED --> ARCHIVED : terminal closure

ARCHIVED --> [*]

note bottom
PUBLISHED means visible/lead-routable.
VERIFIED alone is not enough; catalog, branch/service area
and billing/subscription gates must also pass.
end note
@enduml
